00:16.315 --> 00:22.725
[SPEAKER_34]: Preparing for college is an intimidating process, made a little easier by the Los Angeles Public Library.

00:23.125 --> 00:30.577
[SPEAKER_34]: Their workshop at the Chinatown Branch broke down the application process, highlighted what to expect, and featured a local success story.

00:37.407 --> 00:42.475
[SPEAKER_13]: So today we're here at the Chinatown Branch Library for a Get Ready for College program.

00:43.822 --> 01:00.447
[SPEAKER_25]: We are here today to talk about the college admission process at the Chinatown Public Library as one of the assistant directors of admission and also as someone who's from Chinatown, I think it's a great honor to be able to come here, talk to the students, give a little bit more insight about it and also share my story as well.

01:00.427 --> 01:02.310
[SPEAKER_09]: Oh, we got questions!

01:02.330 --> 01:17.011
[SPEAKER_45]: I showed up to the college workshop today because I am a rising junior and I wanted to know more about the college process and how to be, you know, get a better chance at getting like some colleges like UCs that, you know, are closer to me.

01:17.071 --> 01:21.237
[SPEAKER_00]: Today I want to talk about the pandemic of approaching college habits.

01:21.217 --> 01:24.901
[SPEAKER_04]: Going through college is a hard, long process.

01:25.402 --> 01:28.045
[SPEAKER_04]: Basically, you need to read all the applications yourself.

01:28.085 --> 01:33.712
[SPEAKER_04]: You need to decide whether you want to go to a big school, a small population, what curriculum.

01:34.233 --> 01:44.385
[SPEAKER_04]: So today is more for, instead of you diving through by yourself, there are people here just to walk you through, to guide you through, to give you pointers on where to go to find out more information on what you need.

01:44.525 --> 01:46.988
[SPEAKER_25]: Focus on writing about yourself and your own story.

01:46.968 --> 01:49.833
[SPEAKER_25]: So the difference between college and high school is a lot.

01:49.874 --> 01:53.080
[SPEAKER_25]: I think applying to college, you realize that there's a lot.

01:53.120 --> 01:55.645
[SPEAKER_25]: There's ways to kind of pursue your career for the long run.

01:56.186 --> 01:58.370
[SPEAKER_25]: And also, it's a very different environment.

01:58.390 --> 01:59.973
[SPEAKER_25]: You meet folks from all over the world.

02:00.915 --> 02:02.558
[SPEAKER_25]: You are also learning about yourself.

02:02.578 --> 02:03.700
[SPEAKER_25]: You're living on your own.

02:04.181 --> 02:08.369
[SPEAKER_25]: So I think there's a big difference in terms of just kind of figuring out your purpose.

02:08.469 --> 02:10.613
[SPEAKER_25]: And you're also in an environment to do so.

02:10.593 --> 02:12.897
[SPEAKER_25]: Are there specific topics that students should avoid?

02:13.358 --> 02:20.049
[SPEAKER_45]: I think it's really important right now to get this information since there's so much, you know, misinformation about college.

02:20.389 --> 02:27.140
[SPEAKER_25]: I hope after this event that students are able to kind of feel less intimidated by the college application process.

02:27.201 --> 02:32.570
[SPEAKER_25]: So I hope I was able to give them the confidence to apply and also ask questions and share their story with us.

02:33.271 --> 02:34.693
[SPEAKER_50]: So thank you so much for being here.

